$ ISO 6709

ISO 6709 is defines the representation of geographic point locations (latitude, longitude, altitude) by coordinates.

A point is defined by
  • two mandatory values for the horizontal coordinate (for example latitude and longitude)
  • an optional vertical value (height, depth)
  • an optional identification of the → https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Spatial_reference_system[spatial reference system] (SRS).

Rules:
  • Latitude before longitude (same as EPSG:4326)
  • North latitude and east longitude is positive
  • In digital → development/Data/exchange[data exchange], fraction of degrees are preferred (while → https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sexagesimal[sexagesimal] notation is tolerated).

sa:

  The order of of the coordinates in → tools/Google-Earth/kml[KML files] and → development/languages/JavaScript/JSON/GeoJSON is reversed: first longitude, then latitude.

